MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifDisplay-ExtraCondensedThinItalic', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Display ExtraCondensed Thin Italic' ≠ 'Noto Serif Disp ExtCond Thin Italic' (NID 1 + 'Space' + NID 2).

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Display ExtraCondensed Light' ≠ 'Noto Serif Disp ExtCond Light' (NID 1).

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifDisplay-ExtraCondensed', Everything looks good.

MS NID 16/17

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Display ExtraCondensed Italic' ≠ 'Noto Serif Disp ExtCond Italic' (NID 1 + 'Space' + NID 2).

name

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Display ExtraCondensed Medium' ≠ 'Noto Serif Disp ExtCond Med' (NID 1).

MS NID 16/17

Noto Serif Disp ExtCond Bold (NotoSerifDisplay-ExtraCondensedBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifDisplay-ExtraCondensedBold', Everything looks good.

Noto Serif Disp ExtCond Bold (NotoSerifDisplay-ExtraCondensedBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Display ExtraCondensed Bold' ≠ 'Noto Serif Disp ExtCond Bold' (NID 1 + 'Space' + NID 2).

name

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Display ExtraCondensed ExtraBold' ≠ 'Noto Serif Disp ExtCond ExtBd' (NID 1).
